			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It has yet to stop being fun for me, though my idea of fun is not "happy, fluffy, immediately gratifying and never frustrating".
<br />

<br />
I'm still not sure what people expect in terms of rewards in this game. Yes, true, there's no "win!" moment when the klaxon sounds, confetti falls and you're declared the hero. If that's what you're waiting for, stop. It's never going to happen.
<br />

<br />
If you don't play to progress, and that can mean *many* things, then play to hang out with friends if that's what's fun for you. If you're not having fun, then cancel your subscription and wait until you WANT to renew it. That may be next week, next month, never. But as long as you're unhappy and still logging in, you're wasting time and money in a real sense.
<br />

<br />
Play the game, as the man said; don't let it play you.
<br />

<br />
Edited to add: I petitioned last night because of a name issue - my cleric's last name was rejected. Petition was answered by a guide within an hour, successfully (my sister the cleric has the same last name as me now).<br />_________________<br />Illumine Bahira
<br />
Elementalist of Erudin</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
