				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sure, he brings up valid points. But I disagree with him on one of the most essential;
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The second thing you have to know is that the game stops being fun.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That is because you keep playing when it isn't fun. When the game isn't fun anymore, I stop playing... be it EQ, or any other game. When EQ gets too frustrating, and playing is becomming a task rather than an enjoyment, I stop playing. For a couple hours, couple months, whatever it takes. WHY keep playing the game, if you aren't having fun?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">they all hate Sony – the designers of Everquest.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
